code.apps.chat.util

Class ChatMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • code.apps.chat.util.ChatMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ChatMessage
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    An instance of this class is a message sent in a chat session. Each ChatMessage has some type, specified by ChatMessageType, and some content (a String, which may be empty). Also, it has to be Serializable because for network transport it will be converted to a stream of bits and sent down an ObjectOutputStream then reconstituted back into an object at the other end in an ObjectInputStream.

    This class depends on class ChatMessageType.
